## Dashboard Overview

### Purpose and Scope
**Dashboard Function:**
- Provide real-time visibility into system performance and health
- Enable proactive identification of performance issues and optimization opportunities
- Support data-driven decision making for system improvements
- Track progress toward performance objectives and KPIs

**Coverage Areas:**
- **System Performance:** Overall system responsiveness, availability, and reliability
- **Workflow Performance:** Individual workflow execution metrics and efficiency
- **Context Performance:** Context loading, management, and optimization effectiveness
- **Resource Performance:** Token usage, memory utilization, and computational efficiency
- **Quality Performance:** Rule effectiveness, user satisfaction, and error rates

### Dashboard Structure
```
Performance Monitoring Dashboard
├── Executive Summary (High-level KPIs)
├── System Health Overview (Real-time status)
├── Performance Trends (Historical analysis)
├── Alert Management (Active issues and notifications)
├── Detailed Metrics (Component-level analysis)
└── Optimization Recommendations (Actionable insights)
```

